                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.351/9–1049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-10T20:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 10, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 10—3:19 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2274. Handed note on Dairen Consulate to Vyshinsky at 2005 (urtel 635, September
                    9) and explained briefly its contents. Emphasized clearly our desire for prompt
                    reply and importance we attached to Soviet action, which Vyshinsky acknowledged
                    as evident by my personal intervention. He assured me matter would be dealt with
                    as rapidly as possible, and that he would avail himself of my offer to come
                    personally to receive their answer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
